---
description: Frontend and UI implementation rules
globs: "app/**/*,src/components/**/*,src/features/**/*,src/routes/**/*,pages/**/*,components/**/*"
---

- Prefer user-visible behavior over implementation cleverness. Keep state transitions explicit and easy to trace.
- Preserve accessibility basics by default: labels, keyboard flow, focus visibility, and semantic structure.
- Keep loading, empty, and error states present in the same change when adding UI behavior.
- Avoid mixing API normalization, UI state, and rendering concerns in one file when the feature grows.
- Follow the project architecture, naming, and safety rules in `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md`.

